# Project Title
Admin Panel with Sequelize and nodejs


## Install
  npm install

## Running the project
  npm server.js / nodemon

## Features:
	passportjs authentication
	User can upload image
  User can view, update and delete there information
  User can reset password
	AddressBook can add multiple addresses
	AddressBook can view, update and delete

## Packages
    1) @hapi/joi: For Validation
    2) bcrypt: For Password authentication
    3) body-parser: node.js middleware for handling  the incoming request bodies
    4) cors: Cross-Origin Resource Sharing
    5) dotenv: store the sensitive data
    6) express: Node.js web application framework
    7) express-joi-validation: validate express application inputs and parameters using joi
    8) jsonwebtoken: generate token for authentication
    9) multer: upload image
    10) mysql2: mysql database
    11) nodemon: automatically restarting the node application when file changes in the directory are detected
    12) passport: authentication 
    13) passport-jwt: authentication 
    14) sequelize: database tool
    15) winston: logger
